  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to examine the relative (ICC) and absolute intertester
      reliability of the 6-Minutes Walking Test in hip fracture patients (N=50) in an outpatient
      facility. The data collection is conducted by two physiotherapists, who are blinded to each
      other. The physiotherapists are randomized so they each are doing an equal number of baseline
      tests.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
